---
source: cli/tests/help.rs
expression: "help(&[\"replace\"])"
---
Replace a device in the filesystem.

Replace a device with another device or a spare. During replacement, data is read from the old
device and written to the new one. The replace operation can be monitored and cancelled. Requires
CAP_SYS_ADMIN.

Usage: replace <COMMAND>

Commands:
  start   Replace a device in the filesystem
  status  Print status of a running device replace operation
  cancel  Cancel a running device replace operation
  help    Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
